The paper deals with the problem of approximating the partition function of the hard-core model on graphs, which is a well-studied problem in theoretical computer science and statistical physics. The paper uses techniques from computational complexity theory, graph theory, and probability theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CC (computational complexity), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.GT (discrete mathematics), cs.DM (discrete mathematics), and cs.SI (social and information networks).
